    {
      "id": "sybil_15_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_15",
      "description": "This 1994 Mazda RX-7 (FD3S) is a superlative example of rotary engineering, preserved in its factory-delivered configuration. The 13B-REW power plant features a sequential twin-turbocharger system that delivers a seamless transition and linear torque curve across the RPM range. The chassis retains its original 50/50 weight distribution, supported by a lightweight four-wheel double-wishbone suspension and a Torsen limited-slip differential. Recent diagnostic testing confirms optimal compression across all rotor faces, with the apex seals maintaining a perfect seal. The 5-speed manual gearbox offers precise gate entry, and the braking system utilizes the original four-piston front calipers for consistent thermal management. Finished in pristine Montego Blue Mica with a flawless tan leather interior, this unmodified FD remains a benchmark for 90s JDM performance and mechanical purity.",
      "price": 48500.0,
