    {
      "id": "sybil_19_listing_7",
      "firm_id": "sybil_19",
      "description": "Presented is a superlative 1995 Mazda RX-7 FD3S, a masterclass in lightweight engineering and rotary performance. The heart of this specimen is the 13B-REW power plant, which retains its complex factory sequential twin-turbocharger configuration, providing a seamless transition between the primary and secondary turbines. Compression numbers are high and consistent across all rotor faces, indicative of healthy apex seals and a well-maintained thermal cycle history. The chassis remains true to its 50:50 weight distribution, featuring the original double-wishbone suspension with no discernible bushing deflection. Power is channeled through a precise five-speed manual transmission to a Torsen limited-slip differential, ensuring optimal corner-exit traction. The exterior displays factory-correct paint depth with zero oxidation, while the interior is devoid of the typical plastic delamination or bolster wear. This is a mechanically transparent, investment-grade FD for the discerning purist.",
